<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 31308 allows the Secretary of Commerce or Transportation to foreclose on a lien arising from a right established under a mortgage under title XI of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936. This section makes no substantive change to law.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf6a7b224-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf6a7b225-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2010—<ref href="/us/pl/111/281">Pub. L. 111–281</ref> substituted “The Secretary of Commerce or Transportation, as a mortgagee under this chapter,” for “When the Secretary of Commerce or Transportation is a mortgagee under this chapter, the Secretary”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2006—<ref href="/us/pl/109/304">Pub. L. 109–304</ref> substituted “chapter 537 of this title” for “title XI of the Merchant Marine Act, 1936 (46 App. U.S.C. 1271 et seq.)”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1990—<ref href="/us/pl/101/595">Pub. L. 101–595</ref> substituted “(46 App. U.S.C. 1271 et seq.)” for “(46 App. U.S.C. 1241 et seq.)”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idf6a7b226-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idf6a7b227-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1989-01-01">Jan. 1, 1989</date>, with certain exceptions and qualifications, see <ref href="/us/pl/100/710/s107">section 107 of Pub. L. 100–710</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s31301">section 31301 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
